reviews.text: Delicious food with generous portions, easily among the best spots in the area. However, I was disappointed by how much single-use plastic is used, even for dine-in service. While I understand the need for disposable utensils for take-out orders, it doesn‚Äôt make sense to serve dine-in meals with one-time use plastics. In today‚Äôs world, businesses have a responsibility to reduce their reliance on plastics and embrace more sustainable practices.

Google reviews brought us here and Boro Kabob did not disappoint! They‚Äôve earned their 4.7. We were greeted by Raha, warm, friendly, asked if we were familiar with Persian food, helped explain a few menu items. Great energy and wonderful service from both Raha and Alanah!! The food was fresh, plentiful and delicious. Everything we tried was well seasoned. We tried the lentil soup, and hummus, chicken kabobs and kubiddeh platter with half rice, half salad, and the rose, lime iced tea. Amazing! Looking forward to coming back and trying other dishes, I have a feeling we can‚Äôt go wrong. Fabulous experience and great service from Raha and Alanah! Thank you ladies.

My son wanted to try chicken shawarma, and Boro Kabob was highly recommended on social media. I get the hype now! Raha was very patient with us, and she explained everything thoroughly answered all of our questions. The food was delicious! There are so many more items that I'd like to try. We will definitely be back!

Undoubtedly our favorite restaurant in Columbia. We have been coming here regularly for over a year because the food and service are so good. The kabobs are tender, the rice is perfectly seasoned, the stews are excellent, the pita and various dips come in big portions. I only have good things to say about Boro Kabob. Raha and Arezou are incredible servers. 5/5 stars!

I'm always on the lookout for local Mediterranean style, food and after a trip to s warehouse store in Columbia, Google recommended Boro and boy am I glad they did!

So far I can only speak for the falafel. Shawarma-wich, which was a neat spin on the traditional falafel.

The sandwich was heavy and something that I'm still thinking about!

I can't wait to go by and try some of their other variations...
